        <title>Top publications</title>
        <author>
            <name>Adrien Leger</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://a-slide.github.io/publications-and-communication.html"/>
        <id>https://a-slide.github.io/publications-and-communication.html</id>

        <updated>2020-08-26T00:49:13+01:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/11/books.jpg" alt="" />
                    E Lecomte,&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <img src="https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/11/books.jpg" alt="" />
                <ul>
<li>E Lecomte, B Tournaire, B Cogné, JB Dupont, P Lindenbaum, ... and <strong>A Leger</strong>.<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2162253116300452" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> Advanced characterization of DNA molecules in rAAV vector preparations by single-stranded virus next-generation sequencing, </a>Molecular Therapy-Nucleic Acids 4, e260</li>
</ul>
<pre><em>First publication on rAAV vector quality control by next-generation sequencing. Currently being used for several human gene therapy clinical trials. The method then got refined and published in 3 subsequent papers and reviews.</em></pre>
<ul>
<li><strong>A Leger</strong> and T Leonardi. <a href="https://joss.theoj.org/papers/10.21105/joss.01236" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pycoQC, interactive quality control for Oxford Nanopore Sequencing, </a>Journal of Open Source Software 4 (34), 1236</li>
</ul>
<div>
<pre><em>Although the paper was not published in a high impact journal, this is one of my research project with the highest impact. <a href="https://github.com/a-slide/pycoQC" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pycoQC</a> has gained a lot of popularity in the Nanopore community and was downloaded more than 60,000 times, highlighting that the impact on the research community is much more than a mere impact factor. </em><em>The Journal of Open Source Software is very developer friendly and I enjoyed the open peer review process via Github.</em></pre>
<ul>
<li>B Cogné, R Snyder, P Lindenbaum, JB Dupont, R Redon, P Moullier and <strong>A Leger</strong>. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/nm.3578" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NGS library preparation may generate artifactual integration sites of AAV vectors</a>, Nature medicine 20 (6), 577</li>
</ul>
<div>
<pre><em>Short communication in response <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/nm.3230" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kaeppel et al</a> demonstrating a major flaw in a next generation sequencing method used to detect rAAV vector integration in a clinical trial. The story goes that we were trying to develop a method very similar to theirs and realised thanks to control conditions that the library preparation protocol was generating random artifactual integration sites with a profile extremely similar to the one the published. We were about to abandon the project but decided that the data should be </em><em>published to avoid the flawed protocol being used further in the gene therapy field. </em></pre>
<ul>
<li><strong>A Leger,</strong> PP Amaral, L Pandolfini, C Capitanchik, F Capraro, I Barbieri,... et al. <a data-href="/citations?view_op=view_citation&amp;hl=en&amp;user=SA5LcXgAAAAJ&amp;citation_for_view=SA5LcXgAAAAJ:_Ybze24A_UAC" class="gsc_a_at">RNA modifications detection by comparative Nanopore direct RNA sequencing. </a>BioRxiv, 843136</li>
</ul>
<pre><i>In this work recently released on BioRxiv, we described the first method for accurate detection of several RNA modifications at high spatial and single molecule resolution. This was an <span data-dobid="hdw">exciting</span> bioinformatics co-development experience with <a href="https://cgs.iit.it/research/computational-rna-biology" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tommaso Leonardi</a> resulting in <a href="https://github.com/tleonardi/nanocompore" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NanoCompore</a>, a significant piece of software which is also gaining traction in the field.<br></i></pre>
<ul>
<li><strong>A Leger</strong>, C Le Guiner, ML Nickerson, KMG Im, N Ferry, P Moullier, ... et al. <a href="Adeno-Associated Viral Vector-Mediated Transgene Expression Is Independent of DNA Methylation in Primate Liver and Skeletal Muscle" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Adeno-associated viral vector-mediated transgene expression is independent of DNA methylation in primate liver and skeletal muscle</a><span style="color: var(--text-editor-body-color); font-family: var(--font-base); font-size: inherit; font-weight: var(--font-weight-normal);">. PLoS One 6 (6), e20881</span></li>
</ul>
<pre><i>My main PhD paper about my attempt to find DNA methylation on the rAAV vector genome. I was an early adopter of pyrosequencing (not the high throughput 454 version) to detect CpG methylation after bisulfite conversion. We managed to <span data-dobid="hdw">painstakingly demonstrate that rAAV genomes stay free of DNA methylation throughout the transduction of the host cell.</span></i></pre>
<i><span data-dobid="hdw">Full list available at <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8772-6776"><img loading="lazy" style="padding: 5px;" src="file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/orcid.png" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" srcset="file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/orcid-xs.png 300w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/orcid-sm.png 480w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/orcid-md.png 749w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/orcid-xl.png 1200w"  alt="" width="40" height="40">ORCID</a> and <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SA5LcXgAAAAJ"><img loading="lazy" style="padding: 5px;" src="file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/scholar.png" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" srcset="file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/scholar-xs.png 300w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/scholar-sm.png 480w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/scholar-md.png 749w ,file:///home/aleg/Documents/Publii/sites/adrien-leger/input/media/posts/9/responsive/scholar-xl.png 1200w"  alt="" width="40" height="40">Google Scholar</a><br></span></i></div>
</div>
