<p class=""><span class="md-line md-end-block" ><span class="">I am a </span><span class=""><strong>computational biologist</strong></span> currently working as a senior postdoc at the EMBL-EBI in Ewan Birney's Team. I have a <span class=""><strong>dual background in molecular biology and bioinformatics</strong></span><span class="">. My PhD was at the bench in </span><span class=""><strong>virology</strong></span> and <span class=""><strong>epigenetics</strong></span> at the INSERM 1089 (University of Nantes, France). I had the opportunity to setup my own team in my PhD lab as a junior team leader and to obtain a master's degree in bioinformatics. I then moved to the EMBL-EBI to expend my skills in data analysis and software development. I have been working on a broad range of topics including <span class=""><strong>RNA modifications in cancer</strong></span> and more recently medaka fish <span class=""><strong>functional genomics</strong></span>.</span></p>
